## PERFORMANCE & SCALABILITY TARGETS

### Indexing Performance
- **Throughput:** 100+ documents per minute on standard hardware
- **Batch Embedding:** Process texts in batches of 32 for efficiency
- **Lazy Loading:** Load embedding model only on first use
- **Memory Management:** Stream documents to avoid loading entire collection

### Search Performance
- **Query Latency:** < 1 second for typical queries (10K-50K documents)
- **Searcher Caching:** Cache loaded indexes per collection to avoid reloading
- **Memory Mapping:** Use mmap for large FAISS indexes
- **Index Types:** Support exact (IndexFlatL2) and approximate search

### Scale Targets
- **Maximum Collection Size:** 100,000 documents per collection on single machine
- **Concurrent Collections:** Support dozens of collections simultaneously
- **Query Throughput:** Support 10+ queries per second per collection

### Optimization Strategies
- Batch processing for embeddings
- Lazy model initialization (load on first use)
- Searcher instance caching (avoid reloading indexes)
- Memory-mapped FAISS indexes
- Iterator-based document reading (stream processing)

