## DESIGN CONSTRAINTS & MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS

### Privacy & Security

- **MUST** maintain privacy-first architecture with all processing local
- **MUST** NOT make external calls during indexing or search (except config validation)
- **MUST** use only local embedding models (sentence-transformers)
- **MUST** support offline operation after initial setup

### Architecture & Design

- **MUST** follow three-layer architecture (CLI, Service, Engine)
- **MUST** support protocol-based connector extension
- **MUST** use configuration-driven behavior instead of hardcoding
- **MUST** maintain clear separation of concerns across layers
- **MUST** support both CLI and library usage patterns

### Extensibility

- **MUST** enable new connectors without modifying core code
- **MUST** maintain backward compatibility with existing collections
- **MUST** use Pydantic for all configuration validation
- **MUST** implement graceful error handling and recovery

### Storage & Persistence

- **MUST** support both global (~/.indexed/) and local (./.indexed/) storage modes
- **MUST** maintain consistent storage structure across versions
- **MUST** use manifest files for collection metadata
- **MUST** persist FAISS indexes in binary format for efficiency

### Quality & Maintainability

- **MUST** maintain test coverage above 85%
- **MUST** document all major components and design decisions
- **MUST** follow consistent design patterns across modules
- **MUST** provide clear error messages with actionable guidance

